sections.Learning outcomes:
On successful completion of the course the student will be able to:
Knowledge and understanding
• analyse aspects of spoken and non-verbal human communication;

Competence and skills
• understand and produce written transcriptions of embodied communicative events;
• apply relevant theories and theoretical concepts to a real-world problem in a discussion within the field of specialisation;

Judgement and approach
• draw on the analysis of spoken and non-verbal human communication in order to evaluate relational aspects of meaning;
• appreciate and reflect on the value and the challenges of adopting multiple different perspectives to the study of human communication.
